This paper discusses the ethical motivations for interpretable machine learning and proposes a distinction between descriptive and persuasive explanations. It also discusses the potential for cognitive bias in explanations that threaten transparency. Given these topics, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper touches on issues related to cybersecurity (cs.CR) and privacy (cs.CY), which are also possible sub-categories.
